54
00:06:19,322 --> 00:06:28,226
A video game with visuals, sound, and narrative displayed in text-based form.

55
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:37,595
That could be one possible definition, but even without sound or narrative displayed

56
00:06:37,655 --> 00:06:42,580
in text on screen, you can still call some games a visual novel.

57
00:06:43,481 --> 00:06:45,783
Then what about a game without any visuals?

58
00:06:47,065 --> 00:06:48,266
That wouldn't make any sense.

59
00:06:48,846 --> 00:06:52,070
How can you call a visual novel if it doesn't contain any visuals?

60
00:06:54,072 --> 00:06:55,153
But it is possible.

61
00:06:56,344 --> 00:07:00,686
to create a piece that essentially is the same and

62
00:07:00,786 --> 00:07:04,708
possesses the same principles as a visual novel, even without

