00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:44,041
So then, let me rephrase what I meant.

85
00:08:49,845 --> 00:08:52,827
It's a video game that weighs heavily on narrative.

86
00:08:56,677 --> 00:09:00,179
The essential quality of a visual novel lies in heavy narrative.

87
00:09:00,319 --> 00:09:04,563
However, just because it's narrative heavy, you can't call it a visual novel, since that

88
00:09:04,603 --> 00:09:12,369
would also apply to film, anime, manga, novels, and so on.

89
00:09:12,669 --> 00:09:17,293
At the same time, you can't just add the word game or the game element to something and

90
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:22,417
call it a visual novel, as would also include things like paperback adventure game books.

91
00:09:23,301 --> 00:09:26,201
In sum, there are two elements that make up the essential

92
00:09:26,241 --> 00:09:29,862
quality of a visual novel, a heavy narrative and a video

93
00:09:29,882 --> 00:09:30,102
game.

94
00:09:37,824 --> 00:09:41,264
So let me step away from visual novels for a second here and

95
00:09:41,304 --> 00:09:47,885
talk about sports. Are football and baseball sports? Of course

96
00:09:47,925 --> 00:09:50,866
they are. Then what about darts?

97
00:09:53,633 --> 00:10:05,800
and pool? How about motor racing, shooting, and fishing? And yes, fishing. What about

98
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:16,706
lingerie football? I don't know about you guys, but I say these are all sports because

99
00:10:16,806 --> 00:10:18,567
they require to be athletic.

100
00:10:20,744 --> 00:10:27,847
However, some people may disagree in a similar way that some people think visual novels are

101
00:10:27,887 --> 00:10:28,527
not games.

102
00:10:37,391 --> 00:10:41,313
So, is a visual novel a game or not?

103
00:10:44,974 --> 00:10:45,575
If it isn't…

104
00:10:46,275 --> 00:10:50,757
I would have to go back and re-examine the essential qualities of what makes a visual

105
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:51,157
novel.

106
00:10:53,178 --> 00:10:55,599
I'm going to go ahead and answer the question for us.

107
00:11:03,342 --> 00:11:04,843
A visual novel is a game.

108
00:11:06,963 --> 00:11:11,525
Similar to how darts and fishing are sports, a visual novel is a game.

109
00:11:13,074 --> 00:11:16,897
But why and how and what exactly is a game then?

110
00:11:16,917 --> 00:11:20,979
If being athletic and having great reflexes

111
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:24,942
defines what a sport is, then what is a game?

112
00:11:31,967 --> 00:11:34,949
A game is something with selectivity, is what I think.

113
00:11:35,569 --> 00:11:36,810
To be more specific.

114
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,483
Something where the selection made by the player's decision

115
00:11:42,783 --> 00:11:45,306
changes the history of events or outcome

116
00:11:45,706 --> 00:11:48,169
that takes place within a given set of rules.

117
00:11:50,291 --> 00:11:51,052
Does that make sense?

118
00:11:52,073 --> 00:11:53,555
Well, let me just give you an example.

119
00:12:03,475 --> 00:12:07,539
In Tetris, the player selects how to move the falling blocks

120
00:12:08,099 --> 00:12:10,101
based on a specific set of rules.

121
00:12:11,262 --> 00:12:13,344
Depending on the selection made by the player,

122
00:12:13,364 --> 00:12:17,567
the blocks below changes its form.

123
00:12:19,009 --> 00:12:22,371
This outcome you see is a result of the player's decision

124
00:12:22,852 --> 00:12:24,994
coming into play with the events

125
00:12:25,094 --> 00:12:26,575
that are displayed on screen.

126
00:12:29,618 --> 00:12:31,499
It's the same with a game of chess.

127
00:12:32,545 --> 00:12:38,646
The player selects how to move the piece based on a given rule, and by doing so, the events

128
00:12:38,786 --> 00:12:41,987
or the history of what's taking place on the board is changed.

129
00:12:42,707 --> 00:12:44,687
So that is why chess is also a game.

130
00:12:46,048 --> 00:12:52,829
Darts, poker, tennis, boxing, Call of Duty, Assassin's Creed, Metal Gear, all these are

131
00:12:52,889 --> 00:12:53,249
games.

132
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:59,791
Oh, of course, and so is lingerie football.

133
00:13:02,596 --> 00:13:03,116
And why?

134
00:13:03,877 --> 00:13:06,799
Because the selection made by the player's decision

135
00:13:07,060 --> 00:13:09,422
changes the history of events taking place

136
00:13:09,522 --> 00:13:11,103
within a given set of rules.

137
00:13:11,924 --> 00:13:16,627
If that's the case, we can say that life is a game too.

138
00:13:18,049 --> 00:13:22,893
Because in life, there are rules and selectivity.

139
00:13:26,175 --> 00:13:28,938
It looks like you guys made the right choice or decision

140
00:13:29,078 --> 00:13:32,300
because you are here today listening to me speak.

141
00:13:46,153 --> 00:13:50,316
A game specializing in selectivity, that's a visual novel.

142
00:13:51,877 --> 00:13:58,423
In that sense, I believe it's a category of games in its purest form, a primitive game.

143
00:13:59,243 --> 00:14:04,187
As you know, except for some rare ones, the majority of visual novels have some form of

144
00:14:04,227 --> 00:14:04,908
selectivity.

145
00:14:05,853 --> 00:14:09,935
They are generally displayed in the form of a selection or choice.

146
00:14:10,655 --> 00:14:16,538
This is where visual novels differ from film, anime, manga, and novels.

147
00:14:17,139 --> 00:14:20,360
They might all have narratives, but they don't have selectivity.

148
00:14:21,081 --> 00:14:25,263
The viewer or reader is unable to step into the story at will.

149
00:14:26,023 --> 00:14:28,385
This is the biggest strength for visual novels.

150
00:14:39,014 --> 00:14:43,817
In Japan, visual novels have naturally evolved and developed over time.

151
00:14:45,378 --> 00:14:51,282
Similar to the giant tortoise in the Galapagos Islands, it has evolved in its own unique

152
00:14:51,322 --> 00:14:54,604
way domestically in a closed environment.

153
00:14:57,757 --> 00:15:03,419
And like Charles Darwin's theory of evolution, perhaps someone in the audience will uncover

154
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:07,281
an eccentric idea as well.

155
00:15:09,682 --> 00:15:15,424
The first example is Steins Gate, a visual novel released in 2009 by 5PB Games.

156
00:15:19,382 --> 00:15:22,066
This game does not have any selections or choices.

157
00:15:22,366 --> 00:15:25,210
Instead, there is a selectivity element

158
00:15:25,671 --> 00:15:27,674
where you can either choose to send an email

159
00:15:27,794 --> 00:15:29,136
from your mobile phone or not.

160
00:15:29,536 --> 00:15:32,000
Depending on your selection, the plot changes.

161
00:15:35,686 --> 00:15:42,690
The following year in 2010, our company released a game called Danganronpa, Academy of Hope

162
00:15:42,810 --> 00:15:44,491
and High School Students of Despair.

163
00:15:45,191 --> 00:15:49,874
It is a murder mystery adventure game with a school trial at the center of the story.

164
00:15:50,814 --> 00:15:54,876
